cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.GT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on device-to-device communications underlaying cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the tradeoff between energy efficiency and spectral efficiency, which is a fundamental problem in information theory. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The resource allocation problem is modeled as a noncooperative game, which falls under the scope of game theory. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed algorithm is a distributed energy-efficient resource allocation algorithm, which falls under the scope of systems and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The proposed algorithm and system parameters are analyzed and verified through computer simulations, which falls under the scope of multimedia.
